# Environment Variables Configuration (Production)

For production environments, use this `.env.example` file as a template.

**Important**: 
1. Rename this file to `.env`
2. Never commit `.env` to version control
3. Add `.env` to your `.gitignore`

## Configuration

```
# Email Configuration
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password
RECIPIENT_EMAIL=elde.arotcha@gmail.com
```

## Usage in send_email.php

Replace the hardcoded values with environment variables:

```php
require 'vendor/autoload.php';

// Load environment variables
$dotenv = Dotenv\Dotenv::createImmutable(__DIR__);
$dotenv->load();

$mail->Host = $_ENV['SMTP_HOST'];
$mail->Username = $_ENV['SMTP_USERNAME'];
$mail->Password = $_ENV['SMTP_PASSWORD'];
$mail->addAddress($_ENV['RECIPIENT_EMAIL']);
```

## Install PHP Dotenv

```bash
composer require vlucas/phpdotenv
```

This provides better security for sensitive credentials.
